Job Description & Responsibilities

Assist clients in their China tax compliance obligations, including preparation of tax computations and returns, and handling correspondence with the Mainland Tax Bureau;
Provide China tax advisory and consulting services to clients;
Develop and maintain client relationships;
Manage and develop a team of professional staffs; and
Perform initial client needs analysis, determine the key areas of service that we want to pursue and develop value propositions and pitches for the client
Requirements

A recognised degree holder preferably in accounting or equivalent;
Qualified member of a professional accounting body;
Minimum five to eight years of China tax experience;
Confident with a strong business sense;
Ability and aptitude in managing multiple stakeholders both internally and externally;
Solid project management experience with strong analytical and organizational skills
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills;
Proficient in both written and spoken English; and
Fluency in Putonghua.
In addition, candidates should illustrate the following personal attributes:

Demonstrates courage and integrity
Acquires and applies commercial and technical expertise by staying up to date in industry and with market trends
 Manages projects and economics efficiently; planning and performing work in accordance with client requirements and professional standards 
Open minded, agile with change and practical
Committed to self develop and coaching of others for growth
Communicates with impact and empathy
Actively shares ideas and knowledge and is innovate
Lead and contribute to team success
Is passionate about client service

About Financial Services Tax Practice

Our practice being the largest amongst professional accounting firms in Hong Kong, serves Hong Kong, mainland and international clients in the banking and capital markets, insurance and asset management industries.  We provide tax compliance and consulting services to our clients. 

Job Description

Provide HK tax compliance and consulting services to clients in one of the industries:- retail, financial services, trading, technology, manufacturing, transportation or logistics;
Work with a team of professionals on cross-teams and regional tax advisory and consulting projects, such as public listing, merger and acquisition, group restructuring, transfer pricing study, operations review and tax dispute resolutions; and
Structured training will be provided equipping you to become a professional advisor
Requirements

 University graduate or above;
Qualified member of a professional accounting body is preferred;
Minimum three years of relevant tax experience;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese; Mandarin is a plus

Job Descriptions and Responsibilities

In recent years, the Hong Kong Inland Revenue Department (“IRD”) has been deploying more resources on tax controversy and taking a more stringent approach in handling tax disputes with both corporate and individual taxpayers. Given the adoption of OECD’s action plan on Base Erosion and Profit Shifting (“BEPS”) and the implementation of new tax regulations, taxpayers are facing more challenges and encountering with more tax controversy issues. To cope with the increasing market demand for tax controversy and dispute resolution services, our Tax Controversy Services (“TCS”) team is expanding and now recruiting experienced talents (preferably those who are familiar with the IRD’s practices and/or with practical experience of dealing with the IRD) to join our TCS team.

Our TCS team consists of ex-officers and tax specialists with strong expertise and experience in handling tax controversy. We are currently seeking high caliber tax professionals to join us and take part in:

Assisting clients in resolving tax disputes, for example, tax audit and appeal cases, tax enquiries, challenges on the entitlement to treaty benefits;
Formulation of settlement approaches for tax audit and investigation cases;
Negotiation with the IRD’s officers during the course of case resolving;
Handling simple tax audit cases independently with direct partner supervision;
Post-audit restructuring to rectify problems identified during tax audit;
Conducting tax health checks and defense file building;
Assisting clients in obtaining treaty protection or treaty benefits, and defending against any challenges from the IRD;
Developing and maintaining good client relationship at working level; and
Assisting in the practice development for the TCS team and PwC.

Requirements

A recognized accounting or equivalent degree
Qualified member of a professional accounting body
Total 3- 5 years of experience in Hong Kong profits tax experience, preferably with experience of field audits / tax investigations or other areas of tax controversy
With IRD work experience is a plus, particularly experience in the Field Audit and Investigation Unit, Appeals Section or Treaty Section
Fluent in both written and spoken English, Cantonese and Putonghua
Excellent interpersonal skills would be an advantage
Analytical-minded and solid in project management
Candidates with more experience will be considered for Manager role



The PwC China (including Mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau) does not accept unsolicited resumes from search firm recruiters. Fees will not be paid in the event a candidate submitted by a recruiter without an agreement in place is hired; such resumes will be deemed the sole property of PwC China (including Mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau). PwC China (including Mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau) is an equal opportunity employer. All aspects of employment will be based on merit, competence, performance, and business needs. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, marital status, age, national origin, ancestry, physical or medical condition, genetic information, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, veteran status, or any other status protected under the local law.

Your Key Responsibilities

Assist senior team members to perform various TP and tax analysis including TP planning/advisory, TP documentation, audit defense, advance pricing agreements and other related deliverables;
Analyze clients business activities, financial performance and intercompany transactions;
Participate in meetings or phone calls with senior business executives to identify functions, assets and risks;
Review data sets, and perform financial analysis using a variety of economic, statistical and sector based models or techniques;
Ensure timely delivery of work by managing project workflow, analyzing information, effective (internal and external) communication and managing and coaching more junior members of team;
Conduct industry and company research for clients in a range of sectors;
Closely collaborate with TP or tax teams in HK or across the network;
Monitoring OECD, global or local country TP or related tax developments.

Requirements

2 to 6 years of relevant experience in corporate tax or TP from other accounting firms and industry preferred
Candidates with consulting, advisory, valuation, research, audit or related experience will also be strongly considered
Degree holder, preferably major in economics, accounting, business, mathematics, finance or related disciplines
Excellent command of both written and spoken English; proficiency in Mandarin is preferred
Experience with common technology and TP database tools is important; experience with automation or efficiency solutions is an advantage.

What We Look For

Applicants who are dynamic, motivated and team-oriented.
Critical thinkers with strong numerical and analytical skills
Professionals who are curious and fascinated by the inner working of business
Team player who can work effectively with others to achieve a common goal
Interest and proficiency in new technologies

Remark

Position offered will be commensurate with the experience of the right candidate

