Ensure period-end closing activities to be completed in a timely manner;
Participate in project accounts, forecast and management accounts assignments;
Perform company secretarial tasks;
Perform business correspondence, internal control and ad hoc assignments.

 Requirements:

Bachelor/Higher Diploma or above in Accounting or related disciplines;
At least 2 years' work experience in commercial accounts or audit fields; more experienced with the right calibre may be considered as Deputy Accountant;
Good command of written English; fast and accurate Chinese data-entry and Putonghua preferred;
Familiar with PRC accounting and taxation related regulations and practices is a distinctive advantage;
Good at MS Office and Internet, etc. Habit of logically organizing Windows files and folders;
Mature, energetic and able to work independently. 

We offer competitive remuneration, self- and spouse group medical covering out-patient, in-patient, dental, Chinese medicine practitioner, bank holidays, decent Grade A work environment in Admiralty.

