At least 3 years professional audit experience;
Professional qualifications including HKICPA, ACCA or equivalent;
Good command in written and spoken English, Cantonese and fluency in Putonghua;
A determined team leader with drive and initiative;
Excellent communications and inter-personal skills; and
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.

We offer competitive remuneration packages and attractive staff fringe benefits to the right candidate.  

Interested applicants please submit your full resume, current and expected salary to our Human Resource Department at 5th Floor, Ho Lee Commercial Building, 38-44 D’Aguilar Street, Central, Hong Kong or click “Apply Now”.  Personal data will be collected for recruitment purposes only.

Job Responsibilities

Responsible for the financial and management reporting, budgeting, variance analysis, forecasting, assist in inventory control, VAT processing, and implement or create policies and procedures to control the business as well as proactively identifying and resolving finance and reporting issues;
Manage all aspect of the finance daily operation function in Thailand and PRC manufacturing plant;
Formulate and implement financial policies and maintain effective internal control system for local regulations; 
Involve in analyzing, reviewing and establishing operational and internal system controls effectiveness and procedures;
Evaluate control design and gap analysis; perform testing and evaluate operational effectiveness; identify and remediate deficiencies / weaknesses;
Prepare cash-flow forecast and planning & tax planning;
Ensure compliance with the statutory requirements of audit and tax filing

Job Requirements

Professional qualified accountant with HKICPA or equivalent qualification;
At least 5 years’ accounting/auditing experience and preferably in manufacturing industry;
Solid experience in managing finance/accounting function in PRC;
Familiar with HK & WOFE accounting standards, taxation, regulations and operations;
Experience in computerized accounting and ERP system;
Energetic, good interpersonal skills, disciplinary and task-oriented and able to work independently in dynamic environment;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese, including Putonghua and Cantonese;
Experience in setting up company in Thailand is highly preferred;

Interested parties, please send your full resume stating your expected salary and date of availability to the Human Resources and Administration Department by email for application. We offer successful candidates an attractive remuneration packages (Basic salary + Bonus + Medical Scheme) and the opportunity to work in a dynamic and exciting environment. (Data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only)

Alfred H.K. Li & Co., CPA is a fast-growing and highly dynamic CPA firm in Hong Kong.

Due to continuous business expansion, we are looking for Audit junior, Semi-senior, Senior auditors and Supervisors who are conscientious, independent, responsible and hardworking.

Requirements:

Diploma/Associate Degree/Degree major in Accounting;
Student member of HKICPA/ACCA or equivalent preferred;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese is essential;
Willing to travel to P.R.C. and fluent in Putonghua;
One to four years’ audit experiences in audit firms preferred;
Good command of knowledge in Microsoft Office and accounting software;
Good interpersonal communication skill;
Able to work under pressure and carry out multi-tasks independently;
Hardworking, honest, responsible and self–motivated; and
Immediate available is preferable.

Remuneration will be commensurate with qualification and experiences.   We offer 5 days’ work, discretionary performance bonus, 12 days annual leave, birthday leave, study and examination leaves and medical allowance.

Interested candidates should forward your resume, expected and present salary and date of availability by clicking Apply Now.

