Job Description & Summary



A career in our Corporate Transfer Pricing practice, within Transfer Pricing services, will provide you with the opportunity to help our clients develop compliant, tax efficient structures that help advance their business goals. You’ll focus on all aspects of documentation planning, dispute resolution, and advance pricing agreements.

Our team helps our clients with a range of transfer pricing solutions including compliance, advancing pricing agreements, and defence and dispute resolution. You’ll focus on helping clients with business transformation that ultimately helps advance their business goals.



Job Description &   Responsibilities

Provide HK and China transfer pricing consulting services to clients in one of the industries:- retail, financial services, trading, technology, manufacturing, transportation or logistics;
Work with a team of professionals on cross-teams and regional transfer pricing projects; and
Structured training will be provided equipping you to become a professional advisor.




Requirements

Bachelor degree in Accounting, Economics or Finance;
Minimum 2 years of relevant experience in transfer pricing either in an accounting firm or industry;
Ability to interpret and analyse financial statements and a general aptitude for quantitative analysis;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese; Mandarin is a plus




